					<description><![CDATA[Fantasy football is a game.Â  It should be a fun way to get into football and a good way for friends to generally share some laughs together. This is far from what it is. It has become a complete and whole disdain of my existence.Â  It causes me literally enough frustration to throw and break [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Fantasy football is a game.Â  It should be a fun way to get into football and a good way for friends to generally share some laughs together.</p>
<p>This is far from what it is.</p>
<p>It has become a complete and whole disdain of my existence.Â  It causes me literally enough frustration to throw and break objects in my home.Â  Don&#8217;t get me wrong here &#8211; I&#8217;m generally a very easy going person and don&#8217;t very often let my temper get the better of me.Â  But, for some reason, Fantasy football has the power to turn my Sundays into 12 hour marathons of pure, unbridled, non-filterd, blinding sheer brutality.</p>
<p>I cannot even BEGIN to explain how pissed off I am.</p>
<p>This &#8220;game&#8221; shouldn&#8217;t matter to me this much.Â  I shouldn&#8217;t give a shit less whether I win or lose or by how much.Â  But sitting here tonight I am absolutely in-fucking-furiated.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s why:Â  I AM GETTING <strong>COMPLETELY SCREWED</strong> in Fantasy football.</p>
<p>So many readers might be saying &#8220;stop whining&#8221; or &#8220;suck it up&#8221; or something along those lines &#8211; but before you pass judgment on my attitude and sour mood, please allow me to explain my frustrations.</p>
<p>Currently, I am in a matchup with &#8220;Vanlandw&#8221; &#8211; and I must say that I mean no ill will or offense toward his person &#8211; but his Fantasy football team was 0 &#8211; 4 before playing me.Â  In those 4 losses, his team scored an average of 90 fantasy points per game.Â  This is important so I&#8217;m going to re-iterate:Â  His average points per game this year in Fantasy football is ninety (90) points.Â  He even said to me about our matchup &#8220;well it&#8217;s an easy win for you&#8221;.Â  One more time:Â  Vanlandw&#8217;s team is <strong>WINLESS</strong> and averaging <strong>NINETY</strong> points per game.</p>
<p>Vanlandw has fully admitted multiple times that he has an awful fantasy team.Â  Guys that were expected to be awesome for him have been rancid &#8211; this is no fault of his own and it&#8217;s very unfortunate that he has a bad fantasy football team (<em>LEEEENNNNNNDAAAAAAALLLLLLEEEEE</em>).Â  I share honor and pride with Vanlandw and am glad that we are gladiating against each other.Â  However, I should be destroying him in our contest this week.Â Â  In my first 4 games, my team is averaging 113.75 points per game.Â  You will note that this is 23.75 points higher than Vanlandw&#8217;s team average points per game.</p>
<p>Our current score, with each having one more player remaining, is currently 108 &#8211; 121.Â  Vanlandw is destroying me.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m fine losing to Vanlandw &#8211; losing to a fellow Van is the least of my frustrations.Â  I congratulate him on actually getting a victory this fantasy season.Â  But, for me, this is a trend that has been the case since last season and it has come to the boiling point where I have submitted to my frustrations.</p>
<p>I have a very competitive fantasy team.Â  I feel that I drafted very well amongst a sea of auto-picking teams.Â Â  My team has scored 563 fantasy points so far this season including my score tonight.Â  This amount of points is bested by only the #1 and #2 teams in our league who have 598 and and 584 points respectively.Â  With similar point values; you might think that I&#8217;d be somewhere around the top three.Â  WOULDN&#8217;T THAT BE SOMETHING.Â  But, Vanbergs is currently in 3rd place. Â  My team has more points than his.Â Â  My team is currently in 8th place out of 10 teams.Â  Let that settle in a bit &#8211; 8th place out of 10.Â  Rancid rancid hideous awful place.</p>
<p>This is similar to last year, where my fantasy team actually led the regular season in points but I ended up finishing in 8th place and barely making the &#8220;consolation&#8221; playoff round.</p>
<p>So, the trend has continued where I have put up enough points every week to beat nearly every other person in our league; but the person I happen to be playing puts up season-high numbers to beat me.Â  My team&#8217;s points-against is 598.Â  This means my opponents in 5 weeks have scored an average of 119.6 points per game against me.Â  Compare that to the REST OF THE LEAGUE PLAYING ANYBODY ELSE and the average points per game are:Â  103.7.Â Â  So, any team playing anybody in our league will score an average of 16 points less than the person playing me.Â  Which, holds true this week looking at my contest with Vanlandw.</p>
<p>This has resulted in my team having an abysmal 1-4 record even though I have 100 more points than teams in that same ballpark (7th, 9th places, etc).Â  I&#8217;m really the only big outlier in our league.Â  Most other teams&#8217; point totals are corresponding to the place that they are in and the number of wins/losses that they have.Â  I don&#8217;t feel mine is at all in line.Â  I&#8217;m not sure why this keeps happening &#8211; but I&#8217;ve had enough of the bullshit.Â  There&#8217;s no other way to put it except that I&#8217;m getting screwed.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m done playing fantasy football.</p>
<ul>
<li>Week 1:Â  Payner&#8217;s Eagle defense scores over 40 fantasy points which is simply unheard of by a defense.Â  I lose 112 &#8211; 133 in what I am very confident in calling a &#8220;bad beat&#8221;.</li>
<li>Week 2:Â  I ACTUALLY WIN.Â  142 &#8211; 101.Â  But, only because Devin Brown failed to start the 2 highest scorers on his team.Â  If he had done that, I would have lost &#8211; so I&#8217;m very surprised that did not occur.</li>
<li>Week 3:Â  Skinny&#8217;s entire team puts up double digit numbers across the board just crushing me.Â  114 &#8211; 139.Â  He was projected to have 111 points and I was projected to have 114.Â  yeah.</li>
<li>Week 4:Â  My three WRs combine for 13 points TOTAL in a loss to Flo that I did actually deserve.Â  87 &#8211; 104.</li>
<li>Week 5:Â  Vanlandw is killing me.Â  His 0 &#8211; 4 team is led by Roddy White who of course puts up career high, franchise high 200+ yards receiving with god knows how many touchdowns.Â  Roddy just swings out 32 Fantasy points by himself. Â  Odd &#8211; since Roddy White in the previous 4 games total had 119 receiving yards and 1 TD.Â  A perfect display of what happens when fantasy owners are playing against me.</li>
</ul>
<p>I sit with a 1 &#8211; 4 record with almost no chance of doing well this season even though my team puts up consistently high numbers.Â  Other team&#8217;s players continue to put up career high and just absolute record breaking numbers seemingly only when they are playing against my team.Â  I&#8217;m sick of it.Â  I want my Sundays back.Â  It&#8217;s BS.Â  It pisses me off.Â  And, I&#8217;m done.</p>
<p>*****EDIT****<br />
Just to follow up to this, I&#8217;m going to post last season&#8217;s final standings.</p>
